# Image View

`Dali::Ui::ImageView` displays image resources in a dali-ui app. Image loading is asynchronous by default, and the view provides app-facing controls for loading, fitting, sampling, masking, coloring, and N-patch rendering.

## Table of Contents

- [Create and Update an Image](#create-and-update-an-image)
- [Fit, Crop, and Sample the Image](#fit-crop-and-sample-the-image)
- [Use Placeholders and Loading Signals](#use-placeholders-and-loading-signals)
- [Control Loading and Resource Lifetime](#control-loading-and-resource-lifetime)
- [Apply Color, Alpha, and Masks](#apply-color-alpha-and-masks)
- [Use N-Patch Images](#use-n-patch-images)
- [Property Constants](#property-constants)

## Create and Update an Image

Create an image view with `Dali::Ui::ImageView::New()`, then set the image URL with `SetResourceUrl()`. The fluent setters return `Dali::Ui::ImageView&`, so related image options can be configured in one expression.

```cpp
using namespace Dali;
using namespace Dali::Ui;

ImageView thumbnail = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/profile.png")
  .SetFittingMode(Ui::Image::FittingMode::FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO)
  .SetDesiredWidth(256)
  .SetDesiredHeight(256);
```

Use `GetResourceUrl()` when you need to inspect the current image source, and `Reload()` when the current URL should be loaded again after changing loader-time options.

```cpp
void ReplaceThumbnail(ImageView imageView, const Dali::String& nextUrl)
{
  if(imageView.GetResourceUrl() != nextUrl)
  {
    imageView.SetResourceUrl(nextUrl);
  }

  imageView.Reload();
}
```

`Dali::Ui::ImageView::DownCast()` converts a generic handle back to an image view when the handle points to an image view; otherwise it returns an uninitialized handle.

```cpp
ImageView imageView = ImageView::DownCast(handle);
if(imageView)
{
  imageView.SetResourceUrl("images/updated.png");
}
```

## Fit, Crop, and Sample the Image

`SetFittingMode()` controls how the image is placed inside the view bounds. `Ui::Image::FittingMode::FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO` scales the image to fit while preserving its aspect ratio. `Ui::Image::FittingMode::FILL` stretches to fill the bounds. `Ui::Image::FittingMode::OVER_FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO` preserves aspect ratio and crops overflow. `Ui::Image::FittingMode::CENTER` keeps the original image size.

```cpp
ImageView preview = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/banner.jpg")
  .SetFittingMode(Ui::Image::FittingMode::OVER_FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO);

Ui::Image::FittingMode currentMode = preview.GetFittingMode();
```

Use `SetPixelArea()` to display a normalized sub-region of the image. The `Vector4` value is `(x, y, width, height)`, with each component in normalized image coordinates.

```cpp
ImageView avatar = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/contact-sheet.png")
  .SetFittingMode(Ui::Image::FittingMode::FILL)
  .SetPixelArea(Vector4(0.25f, 0.0f, 0.25f, 0.5f));

Vector4 visibleRegion = avatar.GetPixelArea();
```

Use `SetSamplingMode()` when scaled image quality matters. Desired width and height are loader hints in pixels; call `Reload()` after changing them for an already-loaded resource.

```cpp
ImageView icon = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/icon-large.png")
  .SetDesiredWidth(64)
  .SetDesiredHeight(64)
  .SetSamplingMode(Ui::Image::SamplingMode::BOX_THEN_LINEAR);

icon.SetDesiredWidth(128)
    .SetDesiredHeight(128)
    .Reload();

int desiredWidth = icon.GetDesiredWidth();
int desiredHeight = icon.GetDesiredHeight();
```

`SetImageLoadWithViewSize(true)` asks the loader to use the resolved view size as the image load size. Use it when the displayed size is the useful image size, and avoid combining it with aspect-ratio layout on the same `ImageView` because the view-size load path changes the natural-size value used for layout.

```cpp
ImageView cover = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/cover.jpg")
  .SetFittingMode(Ui::Image::FittingMode::FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO)
  .SetImageLoadWithViewSize(true);

bool loadsAtViewSize = cover.IsImageLoadWithViewSizeEnabled();
```

## Use Placeholders and Loading Signals

`SetPlaceholderUrl()` sets an image shown while the main resource is loading. `ResourceReadySignal()` is emitted with a `Dali::Ui::View` when the image resource has finished loading and is ready to display.

```cpp
class Gallery
{
public:
  ImageView CreatePhoto()
  {
    ImageView image = ImageView::New()
      .SetPlaceholderUrl("images/placeholder.png")
      .SetResourceUrl("images/photo.jpg")
      .SetFittingMode(Ui::Image::FittingMode::FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO);

    image.ResourceReadySignal().Connect(this, &Gallery::OnImageReady);
    return image;
  }

private:
  void OnImageReady(View view)
  {
    ImageView image = ImageView::DownCast(view);
    if(image)
    {
      Dali::String loadedUrl = image.GetResourceUrl();
    }
  }
};
```

`GetLoadingStatus()` returns the current `Ui::Visual::ResourceStatus` for the image visual. This is useful for status checks around placeholder and reload flows.

```cpp
void RefreshImage(ImageView image)
{
  image.Reload();

  Ui::Visual::ResourceStatus status = image.GetLoadingStatus();
  (void)status;
}
```

## Control Loading and Resource Lifetime

`SetLoadPolicy()` controls when the image starts loading. `Ui::Image::LoadPolicy::IMMEDIATE` loads without waiting for scene attachment. `Ui::Image::LoadPolicy::ATTACHED` defers loading until the view is attached to the scene.

```cpp
ImageView image = ImageView::New()
  .SetLoadPolicy(Ui::Image::LoadPolicy::ATTACHED)
  .SetResourceUrl("images/deferred.jpg");

Ui::Image::LoadPolicy loadPolicy = image.GetLoadPolicy();
```

`SetReleasePolicy()` controls when the image texture can be released from the cache. `Ui::Image::ReleasePolicy::DETACHED` releases when the visual is detached from the scene, `Ui::Image::ReleasePolicy::DESTROYED` releases when the visual is destroyed, and `Ui::Image::ReleasePolicy::NEVER` keeps it cached.

```cpp
ImageView reusable = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/tab-background.png")
  .SetReleasePolicy(Ui::Image::ReleasePolicy::NEVER);

Ui::Image::ReleasePolicy releasePolicy = reusable.GetReleasePolicy();
```

Use `SetSynchronousLoading()` only for cases where synchronous loading is acceptable for the app flow. `SetFastTrackUpload()` requests the fast-track loading path, which is used only when the image visual meets the implementation constraints such as attached loading, detached release, non-synchronous loading, and no alpha-mask URL. `SetOrientationCorrection()` applies EXIF orientation metadata automatically.

```cpp
ImageView detail = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/camera-photo.jpg")
  .SetSynchronousLoading(false)
  .SetFastTrackUpload(true)
  .SetOrientationCorrection(true);

bool sync = detail.IsSynchronousLoading();
bool fastTrack = detail.IsFastTrackUploadEnabled();
bool orientationCorrection = detail.IsOrientationCorrectionEnabled();
```

## Apply Color, Alpha, and Masks

`SetImageColor()` applies a `UiColor` multiplier to the image. Use it for tinting or fading image content independently of the image URL.

```cpp
ImageView tinted = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/symbol.png")
  .SetImageColor(UiColor(1.0f, 0.2f, 0.2f, 1.0f));

UiColor tint = tinted.GetImageColor();
```

Use `SetPreMultipliedAlpha()` when the source image data uses pre-multiplied alpha.

```cpp
ImageView overlay = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/overlay.png")
  .SetPreMultipliedAlpha(true);

bool preMultiplied = overlay.IsPreMultipliedAlpha();
```

`SetAlphaMaskUrl()` applies the alpha channel of a mask image to the main image. `SetCropToMask(true)` crops to the mask bounds. `SetMaskingMode()` selects whether masking is applied during rendering or loading.

```cpp
ImageView masked = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/profile.jpg")
  .SetAlphaMaskUrl("images/circle-mask.png")
  .SetCropToMask(true)
  .SetMaskingMode(Ui::Image::MaskingType::MASKING_ON_RENDERING)
  .SetFittingMode(Ui::Image::FittingMode::FIT_KEEP_ASPECT_RATIO);

Dali::String maskUrl = masked.GetAlphaMaskUrl();
bool cropToMask = masked.IsCropToMask();
Ui::Image::MaskingType maskingMode = masked.GetMaskingMode();
```

When changing mask resources or loader-time masking behavior after the image has loaded, call `Reload()`.

```cpp
void ChangeMask(ImageView image, const Dali::String& maskUrl)
{
  image.SetAlphaMaskUrl(maskUrl)
       .SetMaskingMode(Ui::Image::MaskingType::MASKING_ON_LOADING);

  image.Reload();
}
```

## Use N-Patch Images

`SetNPatchBorder()` configures N-patch border insets as `(left, top, right, bottom)` pixel values. A non-zero border activates N-patch rendering for scalable image backgrounds.

```cpp
ImageView panel = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/panel.9.png")
  .SetNPatchBorder(Vector4(12.0f, 12.0f, 12.0f, 12.0f));

Vector4 border = panel.GetNPatchBorder();
```

Use `SetNPatchBorderOnly(true)` when only the border regions should be rendered and the center should be omitted.

```cpp
ImageView frame = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/frame.9.png")
  .SetNPatchBorder(Vector4(16.0f, 16.0f, 16.0f, 16.0f))
  .SetNPatchBorderOnly(true);

bool borderOnly = frame.IsNPatchBorderOnly();
```

`SetDepthIndex()` changes the image visual depth order inside the same layer. Higher depth indices render on top of lower ones.

```cpp
ImageView foreground = ImageView::New()
  .SetResourceUrl("images/foreground.png")
  .SetDepthIndex(10);
```

## Property Constants

Prefer the typed setters such as `SetResourceUrl()`, `SetFittingMode()`, and `SetLoadPolicy()` in application code. The `Dali::Ui::ImageView::Property` constants expose image-view property indices for systems that need `Dali::Handle::GetProperty()` or `SetProperty()` access.

`Dali::Ui::ImageViewPropertyIndex` is the backing index definition for the image view property range. `Dali::Ui::ImageView::Property::IMAGE` maps to `Dali::Ui::ImageViewPropertyIndex::IMAGE`, and the same relationship exists for the other image view properties.

```cpp
int imageProperty = ImageView::Property::IMAGE;
int fittingProperty = ImageView::Property::FITTING_MODE;
int pixelAreaProperty = ImageView::Property::PIXEL_AREA;

int imageIndex = ImageViewPropertyIndex::IMAGE;
int pixelAreaIndex = ImageViewPropertyIndex::PIXEL_AREA;

(void)imageProperty;
(void)fittingProperty;
(void)pixelAreaProperty;
(void)imageIndex;
(void)pixelAreaIndex;
```

The image view property surface includes `ImageView::Property::IMAGE`, `ImageView::Property::PLACEHOLDER_IMAGE`, `ImageView::Property::FITTING_MODE`, `ImageView::Property::SAMPLING_MODE`, `ImageView::Property::DESIRED_WIDTH`, `ImageView::Property::DESIRED_HEIGHT`, `ImageView::Property::IMAGE_COLOR`, `ImageView::Property::PIXEL_AREA`, `ImageView::Property::ALPHA_MASK_URL`, `ImageView::Property::CROP_TO_MASK`, `ImageView::Property::MASKING_MODE`, `ImageView::Property::LOAD_POLICY`, `ImageView::Property::RELEASE_POLICY`, `ImageView::Property::SYNCHRONOUS_LOADING`, `ImageView::Property::FAST_TRACK_UPLOADING`, `ImageView::Property::IMAGE_LOAD_WITH_VIEW_SIZE`, `ImageView::Property::ORIENTATION_CORRECTION`, `ImageView::Property::PRE_MULTIPLIED_ALPHA`, `ImageView::Property::N_PATCH_BORDER`, and `ImageView::Property::N_PATCH_BORDER_ONLY`.
